external_knowledge:
- 'best-matched clothing items' refers to the top-ranked items based on stock quantity in descending order; 
- 'total stock' is the sum of stock quantities of the top-matched items for each customer;
- 'average price per customer' is the average price of the top-matched items for each customer;
- 'stock left over after accounting for the average price' means the total stock quantity minus the average price per customer (floored to the nearest integer).
